From: Roy Pledge <roy.pledge@nxp.com>
Date: Thu, 25 Apr 2019 10:18:12 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 518/741] soc/fsl/qbman: Fix drain_mr_fqni()

commit 77e68162c85a0788c5ba9ae4ff5ed7e18d529f59 from
http://source.codeaurora.org/external/qoriq/qoriq-components/linux

The drain_mr_fqni() function may be called fron uninterruptable
context so convert the msleep() to an mdelay().  Also ensure that
the valid bit is updated while polling.

Signed-off-by: Roy Pledge <roy.pledge@nxp.com>
Signed-off-by: Zhantao Tang <zhantao.tang@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/soc/fsl/qbman/qman.c | 4 +++-
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/soc/fsl/qbman/qman.c b/drivers/soc/fsl/qbman/qman.c
index baf35966e18f..e072b31f152f 100644
--- a/drivers/soc/fsl/qbman/qman.c
+++ b/drivers/soc/fsl/qbman/qman.c
@@ -1165,6 +1165,7 @@ static int drain_mr_fqrni(struct qm_portal *p)
 {
 	const union qm_mr_entry *msg;
 loop:
+	qm_mr_pvb_update(p);
 	msg = qm_mr_current(p);
 	if (!msg) {
 		/*
@@ -1181,7 +1182,8 @@ static int drain_mr_fqrni(struct qm_portal *p)
 		 * entries well before the ring has been fully consumed, so
 		 * we're being *really* paranoid here.
 		 */
-		msleep(1);
+		mdelay(1);
+		qm_mr_pvb_update(p);
 		msg = qm_mr_current(p);
 		if (!msg)
 			return 0;
